ROCm MoE expert-major regrouping for prefill

Status: PROPOSED (codex recommendation 2026-05-09)

Goal:
Implement expert-major routed MoE prefill so ds4_metal_routed_moe_batch_tensor()
groups the n_tokens prompt's selected experts and reuses IQ2_XXS/Q2_K expert
weight rows across tokens selecting the same expert.  Preserve the public
wrapper signature; keep decode (n_tokens=1) on the existing wave-per-row path
unless the grouped path is proven neutral.

Why:
Codex perf analysis (2026-05-09) ranked this as the #1 remaining prefill
lever.  Canonical 21-token prompt has 126 (token, expert) pairs touching
~80 unique experts -> ~1.58x avoidable expert-weight rereads in routed MoE
prefill.  After FlashAttention (committed 7771ea3), MoE prefill traffic is
the dominant remaining bandwidth cost.  Estimated 1.4-1.6x MoE-portion
speedup, 1.15-1.35x end-to-end prefill.

